{{Infobox royalty |name = Princess Reishi |succession = [[Empress consort of Japan]] |reign = 1108–1134 |succession1 = [[Grand empress dowager of Japan]] |reign1 = 1134–1144 |consort = yes |spouse = |issue = |royal house = [[Imperial House of Japan]] |father = [[Emperor Shirakawa]] |mother = [[Fujiwara no Kenshi (1057–1084)]] |birth_date = 1078 |birth_place = |death_date = {{death year and age|1144|1078}} |death_place = |burial_date = |burial_place = |}}
'''Princess Reishi''' (1078–1144) was a [[Empress of Japan|Japanese Empress]] during the late [[Heian period]]. She was appointed [[Junbo-Ritsugō|honorary mother]] (''junbo'') of her nephew [[Emperor Toba]] and served as empress during his reign. She held the title from 1108 through 1134.<ref name=":3">{{Cite book |last=Venning |first=Timothy |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=M2bFEAAAQBAJ&dq=Sukeko&pg=PT276 |title=A compendium of world sovereigns: Volume II Medieval |publisher=Routledge |year=2023 |isbn=978-1-032-36198-7}}</ref>
== Biography == She was the daughter of [[Emperor Shirakawa]] and [[Fujiwara no Kenshi (1057–1084)]]. Her father abdicated in favor of her brother in 1087. In 1107, her brother [[Emperor Horikawa]] died and was succeeded by her four-year-old nephew, [[Emperor Toba]]. She was appointed to serve ceremoniously as the empress of her nephew in 1108.
In 1130, she ordained as a Buddhist nun.<ref>{{cite web |title=令子内親王 |url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E4%BB%A4%E5%AD%90%E5%86%85%E8%A6%AA%E7%8E%8B-1121071 |website=コトバンク |publisher=The Asahi Shimbun Company |accessdate=2019-10-13 |language=Japanese}}</ref>
