'''Princess Reishi''' (1078–1144) was a {{ill|Empress of Japan|en|Empress of Japan|WD=Q595038|lt=Japanese Empress|1=Empress of Japan}} during the late {{ill|Heian period|en|Heian period|WD=Q193292|lt=Heian period|1=Heian period}}.  She was appointed {{ill|Junbo-Ritsugō|en|Junbo-Ritsugō|WD=Q10895773|lt=honorary mother|1=Junbo-Ritsugō}} (''junbo'') of her nephew {{ill|Emperor Toba|en|Emperor Toba|WD=Q349284|lt=Emperor Toba|1=Emperor Toba}} and served as empress during his reign. She held the title from 1108 through 1134.<ref name=":3">{{Cite book |last=Venning |first=Timothy |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=M2bFEAAAQBAJ&dq=Sukeko&pg=PT276 |title=A compendium of world sovereigns: Volume II Medieval |publisher=Routledge |year=2023 |isbn=978-1-032-36198-7}}</ref>

== Biography ==
She was the daughter of {{ill|Emperor Shirakawa|en|Emperor Shirakawa|WD=Q60949|lt=Emperor Shirakawa|1=Emperor Shirakawa}} and {{ill|Fujiwara no Kenshi (1057–1084)|en|Fujiwara no Kenshi (1057–1084)|WD=Q5507520|lt=Fujiwara no Kenshi (1057–1084)|1=Fujiwara no Kenshi (1057–1084)}}. Her father abdicated in favor of her brother in 1087. In 1107, her brother {{ill|Emperor Horikawa|en|Emperor Horikawa|WD=Q464267|lt=Emperor Horikawa|1=Emperor Horikawa}} died and was succeeded by her four-year-old nephew, {{ill|Emperor Toba|en|Emperor Toba|WD=Q349284|lt=Emperor Toba|1=Emperor Toba}}. She was appointed to serve ceremoniously as the empress of her nephew in 1108.  

In 1130, she ordained as a Buddhist nun.<ref>{{cite web |title=令子内親王 |url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E4%BB%A4%E5%AD%90%E5%86%85%E8%A6%AA%E7%8E%8B-1121071 |website=コトバンク |publisher=The Asahi Shimbun Company |accessdate=2019-10-13 |language=Japanese}}</ref>

